<LEADPARA>  Carrying enough belongings for three days but enough fears for a lifetime,
about 14,500 Americans fled the U.S.-run Clark Air Base on Monday in the
shadow of a huge volcano belching thick plumes of dark ash and steam.;   
Thousands of cars and vans, loaded with children and canaries, dogs and duffel
bags, inched bumper-to-bumper down a winding two-lane road toward safety at
the giant Subic Bay Naval Base on Luzon's west coast. The 48-mile trip took up
to six hours under a blazing sun, leaving both cars and tempers overheated.  </LEADPARA>
